## Current Architecture Snapshot (By Responsibility)

### Ingestion Responsibility
- Pull live meteorology + pollutants + sensor validation asynchronously.
- Normalize/fuse data.
- Publish to Redis streams as system truth.

### Modeling Responsibility
- Use grid/wind/plume state to derive edge toxicity representation.

### Matching Responsibility
- Allocate commuters across candidate corridors under capacity and vulnerability-aware preferences.

### Routing/API Responsibility
- Serve toxicity-aware route outputs and audit traces.
- Consume latest state from Redis.

## Important Compatibility Notes

1. Legacy ingestion files still exist and are partially documented in older docs.
2. Both old and new ingestion concepts currently coexist in repository history/state.
3. Router remains wired to legacy latest-state helper while new streams are also available.
4. New docs were added, but root docs may still include legacy wording in some places.

## Net Result of March Work

- The codebase moved from a primarily legacy/simulated ingestion approach toward a real-time async external API ingestion architecture.
- Redis was evolved from single-stream usage toward a multi-stream shared-truth model while preserving backward compatibility.
- Matching and routing logic became significantly richer with preference-aware, capacity-aware commuter allocation.
- Tooling, documentation, and test coverage were expanded to support implementation and migration.

